about.description:
Tox is a generic virtualenv management and test command line tool you can use for
- checking your package installs correctly with different Python versions and interpreters
- running your tests in each of the environments, configuring your test tool of choice
- acting as a frontend to Continuous Integration servers, greatly reducing boilerplate
  and merging CI and shell-based testing.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.24.5" %}

package:
  name: tox
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/t/tox/tox-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 67e0e32c90e278251fea45b696d0fef3879089ccbe979b0c556d35d5a70e2993

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv
  entry_points:
    - tox = tox:cmdline
    - tox-quickstart = tox._quickstart:main

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools_scm
  run:
    - python
    - colorama >=0.4.1  # [win]
    - filelock >=3.0.0
    - importlib_metadata >=0.12  # [py<38]
    - packaging >=14
    - pluggy >=0.12.0
    - py >=1.4.17
    - six >=1.14.0
    - toml >=0.9.4
    - virtualenv !=20.0.0,!=20.0.1,!=20.0.2,!=20.0.3,!=20.0.4,!=20.0.5,!=20.0.6,!=20.0.7,>=16.0.0

test:
  requires:
    - pip
  imports:
    - tox
  commands:
    - pip check
    - tox --version
    - tox-quickstart --version

about:
  home: https://github.com/tox-dev/tox
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: virtualenv-based automation of test activities
  description: |
    Tox is a generic virtualenv management and test command line tool you can use for
    - checking your package installs correctly with different Python versions and interpreters
    - running your tests in each of the environments, configuring your test tool of choice
    - acting as a frontend to Continuous Integration servers, greatly reducing boilerplate
      and merging CI and shell-based testing.
  doc_url: https://tox.readthedocs.org
  dev_url: https://github.com/tox-dev/tox
  doc_source_url: https://github.com/tox-dev/tox/tree/3.14.3/docs

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - cshaley
    - kalefranz
    - sannykr
    - bollwyvl
